default4.4 
defaultIt is estimated that without GM, additional plantings of 5.1 million hectares of soybeans, 5.6 million h
defaultectares of corn, 
defaultand three
default million hectares of cotton and 350,000 hectares of rape seed would have been globally required in 2010 to maintain existing output.
