default4.5 
defaultIn 2013, supported by national governments and UNESCO, the International Service for the Acq
defaultuisition of Agri-biotech Applications (ISAAA) calculated the effects of GM crops on the environment. It concluded that GM crops alone saved the equivalent of 473 million kilograms of pesticides in 2011, saved 109 million hectares of new land being ploughed
default up and reduced greenhouse gas emissions by 23 billion kilograms of carbon dioxide equivalent.
